      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): prevent recursive task execution during model fallback",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen a session's primary model becomes unavailable mid-session and a fallback model serves a turn that was triggered by an internal completion announcement, the fallback can misread the announced report as a directive and spawn duplicate work. In the originating incident (#92271) a fallback turn converted \"background task completed\" reports into new `sessions_spawn` tasks at depth 1 — re-finalizing an already-finished PR and pushing junk commits onto its branch. `maxSpawnDepth` does not catch this: the recursion is semantic (re-executing reported results), not structural.\n\n## Invariant\n\n> A fallback turn replying to completion announcements must not re-execute or re-spawn work already reported as completed.\n\nDefined once at the shared fallback/run boundary, then enforced per surface — per the review feedback.\n\n## Changes\n\n1. **Completion announcements are marked as evidence (all harnesses).** `buildAnnounceReplyInstruction` (`src/agents/subagent-announce.ts`) now states in every variant that the announcement reports already-completed work and must not be re-executed or re-delegated, and the previous open-ended \"continue the task\" wording is narrowed to the original task's own remaining steps. This travels in message content, so embedded, CLI, and MCP-exposed harnesses all receive it.\n2. **Fallback turns are identified mechanically.** `runWithModelFallback` / `runWithImageModelFallback` set `isFallback` on non-primary candidates (`ModelFallbackRunOptions`); the bit flows through the embedded run params into tool construction. Primary attempts keep their exact previous call shape.\n3. **Work-spawning is blocked at the tool choke point.** `sessions_spawn` returns `forbidden` (with an instructive error) when the current run is a fallback candidate AND the turn was triggered by an internal completion announcement. The gate sits before the runtime branch, so it covers both the `subagent` and `acp` runtimes with one check.\n4. **Completion-announce detection is a shared predicate.** `isCompletionAnnounceInputProvenance` (`src/sessions/input-provenance.ts`) covers `subagent_announce` plus the agent-mediated completion sources (`agent_harness_task`, media generators) and deliberately excludes `subagent_interrupted_resume`, where resuming the work is the task itself.\n\n## Coverage matrix (per review)\n\n| Surface | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Embedded runtime (`sessions_spawn`, subagent + ACP runtimes) | Mechanically enforced, unit-tested |\n| CLI / MCP harnesses | Covered by the content-level evidence guard in the announcement itself |\n| Codex-native `spawn_agent` | Owned by the `codex-rs` tool registry (`multi_agents_spec.rs`); not exposed through this repo's spawn path. Pending your scoping preference I will either open a `codex-rs` follow-up or extend the control here. |\n\n## Tests\n\n- `sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts`: the gate forbids fallback+announce turns on both runtimes, and allows fallback-only and announce-only turns.\n- `input-provenance.test.ts`: predicate coverage including the resume exclusion.\n- `model-fallback.probe.test.ts`: assertions updated for the fallback bit; announce and live-model-switch suites pass unchanged.\n- `pnpm tsgo` and `pnpm tsgo:test` are clean locally.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** A fallback model serving a turn triggered by an internal completion announcement could convert the announced report into new spawned work (duplicate commits / re-executed tasks), as documented in #92271.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Real OpenClaw runtime source from this branch executed on Linux (WSL2 Ubuntu, Node 22) via tsx against a freshly initialized isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME`. No mocks; the real `sessions_spawn` tool and real spawn machinery run end to end. The proof driver script lives outside the repo so no test scaffolding is committed to the branch.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\ncd <branch-checkout> && pnpm exec tsx /home/<user>/openclaw-pr92011-proof.mts\n# driver: creates an isolated OPENCLAW_HOME, builds the real sessions_spawn tool via\n# createSessionsSpawnTool(...) once with { isFallbackRun: true, completionAnnounceTriggered: true }\n# (incident shape) and once without (normal turn), and executes the same spawn request on both.\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Copied live console output from the run above.\n\nScenario A — fallback turn + completion announcement (the #92271 incident shape):\n\n```text\n=== A: fallback turn + completion announcement (must be forbidden) ===\n{\n  \"status\": \"forbidden\",\n  \"error\": \"sessions_spawn is not allowed in this turn: a fallback model is replying to an internal completion announcement. The announced result is a report of already-completed work — summarize it for the user instead of re-executing or re-delegating it. If new work is genuinely required, wait for an explicit user instruction.\"\n}\n```\n\nScenario B — identical request on a normal turn (gate must not trip; request reaches the real spawn machinery, creating a real child session key and run id, then stops only at gateway credentials in the bare proof environment):\n\n```text\n=== B: normal turn, same request (gate must not trip) ===\n{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"error\": \"gateway agent requires credentials before opening a websocket\\nFix: configure gateway.auth token/password, pair this device, or pass --token/--password.\\nConfig: /tmp/openclaw-proof-PjbSSB/.openclaw/openclaw.json\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:95390638-9bac-4529-ae14-4f913e9af288\",\n  \"runId\": \"f690c275-cb30-4afd-8680-b23355e8af2d\"\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The incident-shaped turn is refused with a `forbidden` status and an instructive message, while the identical request on a normal turn passes the gate and proceeds into the real spawn machinery — no false positive.\n\n**Before evidence:** Documented in #92271 from a real production setup: redacted session-log and task-registry evidence showing a fallback turn spawning depth-1 duplicate tasks (including the verbatim task text \"I am passing this task because I lack the terminal execution tool\") and pushing a junk commit onto an open PR branch.\n\n**What was not tested:** A live end-to-end provider-quota exhaustion forcing a real mid-session fallback (requires burning provider quota and a full gateway/channel setup); the fallback bit itself is covered by `model-fallback.probe.test.ts`. Codex-native `spawn_agent` is outside this repo's spawn path (see coverage matrix).\n\nFixes #92271\n",
        "branch": "fix/fallback-recursive-task-execution",
